<a name="t"></a>
<p>Peaceful look the rooftops that timidly tower up amidst the impressive scenery of innumerable lush pine trees. This is Dalat – a place where time becomes meaningless against its beauty. Numb senses are reawakened as you listen to the sound of Mother Nature, watch the light embrace the pure water with a silver shimmer, feel the soothing kindness of an eternal spring day, gain new courage in every single breath and make peace with the unrest of life.</p>
<p> </p>
</div>
<br clear="all"/><div class="grid_8"><h2>Few facts about Dalat:</h2></div><div class="richtext grid_8">
<a name="t"></a>
<ul><li>Dalat is located in Lam Dong province, approximately 200 km northeast of Ho Chi Minh City. At an elevation of 1,500 m, Dalat bears the look of an Old French city. It was founded in 1897 when Doctor Alexandre Yersin recommended that the area be developed as a resort town.</li>
    <li>Surrounded by mountains and pine forests, Da Lat has many characteristics of a temperate climate. The average temperature here is 18–21°C, with highest temperature 30°C and lowest 5°C.</li>
    <li>Dalat also has the two season climate typical of South Vietnam, with a monsoon season from May to October and a dry season from November to April. Dalat is in the temperate region and has pleasant weather year-round, even sunny during much of the rainy season.</li>
    <li>Ideal weather is from November to March, when the air is fresh and cool and the blossom season of every flower.</li>
</ul><p> </p>
</div>
